I-Frame (small) Models


Smith & Wesson Model 30—A small six-shot .32-caliber revolver.[29]
Smith & Wesson Model 32—"Terrier" A small five-shot revolver chambered in .38 S&W .38-caliber. Coil or flat mainspring, round front sight, 2" barrel.[29]
Kit Gun—"Kit Gun" From 1953 to 1958, it was called the 'Model of 1953'. In 1958, it became the model 34. It was blued, chambered in 22LR with a 2" or 4" barrel and adjustable sights.[29] The model 34-1 moved up to the J-Frame.
Smith & Wesson Model 35—A Small six-shot target revolver with adjustable sights and six inch barrel chambered in .22 LR. 22/32 Target Model of 1953. Produced from 1953 to 1973.[29]




